ion of the time needed for\neach card.","position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1},"end":{"line":113,"column":1}},"key":"XBwdC6PHTr"}],"key":"C08BCBz56B"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As the week progresses, I mark off the hours that I’ve spent on each card.","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"Ah7D23CIw6"}],"key":"jm88vlPWU4"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When the card’s hours remaining reaches 0, I move it to the “Done” list","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"yghpe2D3rW"}],"key":"eB3qLdU6Zs"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":118,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At the end of the week, I click my “board cleanup” link, and it returns each card to its\noriginal project board.","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"JdVjKYcLxL"}],"key":"U3B7WoQgMw"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next week, I repeat this cycle.","position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"key":"jCgWSw28Iu"}],"key":"oepIImyXmX"}],"key":"dE9qsZYvS4"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":123,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"And that’s about it - I’ve found that this process is a nice way to keep both a high-level\nview of what needs to be done for my various projects (on each project board). It also allows\nmy to dig into specific to-do items throughout the week (on my weekly board).","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":121,"column":1}},"key":"erLQ14m